# Auto-play Video After Unlock

The user wants the video to start playing immediately after it is successfully unlocked. Currently, the UI updates but the video remains paused.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> We need to ensure that `selectedVideo` in [CircleVideos.tsx](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/circles/CircleVideos.tsx) is kept in sync with the refreshed data from the [useCircleVideos](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/hooks/useCircleVideos.ts#29-298) hook after invalidation.

## Proposed Changes

### [CircleVideos.tsx](file:///c:/Users/elink/./heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/circles/CircleVideos.tsx)

#### [MODIFY] [CircleVideos.tsx](file:///c:/Users/elink/./heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/circles/CircleVideos.tsx)
- Synchronize `selectedVideo` with the latest video data from the `videos` array.
- This ensures that when the query is invalidated and refetched, the [CircleVideoPlayer](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/circles/CircleVideoPlayer.tsx#34-445) receives the updated `user_has_unlocked: true` property.

### [CircleVideoPlayer.tsx](file:///c:/Users/elink/./heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/circles/CircleVideoPlayer.tsx)

#### [MODIFY] [CircleVideoPlayer.tsx](file:///c:/Users/elink/./heart-lens-studio-main/src/components/circles/CircleVideoPlayer.tsx)
- Add a `useEffect` hook to watch for changes in `video.user_has_unlocked`.
- When `user_has_unlocked` transition from `false` to `true`, trigger `videoRef.current.play()` and set `isPlaying` to `true`.
- Ensure handle case where `videoRef.current` might not be immediately available (though it should be once `isLocked` is false).

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  Open a premium video that is locked.
2.  Click the "Unlock" button and pay the coins.
3.  Verify that:
    -   The lock overlay disappears.
    -   The video starts playing automatically.
    -   The play/pause button state updates to "Pause".
